actice, gender dynamics, and church economics. Focusing on the promises and problems that Pentecostalism presents, Moving by the Spirit highlights this religion's role in making life possible in structurally adjusted Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aPentecostalismxSocial aspectszZambiazCopperbelt Province. 0aPentecostalszZambiazCopperbelt ProvincexSocial life and customs. 70(DE-601)1057599450(DE-588)4122782-7aAlltagskultur2gnd 70(DE-601)1058310690(DE-588)4113211-7aCharismatische Bewegung2gnd 70(DE-601)1063703080(DE-588)4008017-1aBrauchtum2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967434423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520967434.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles